<subSubSection pageId="304" pageNumber="441" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="304.[113,647,1610,1699]" box="[113,203,1610,1636]" pageId="304" pageNumber="441">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="304.[113,647,1610,1699]" lastBlockId="304.[674,1212,216,495]" pageId="304" pageNumber="441">
<bibRefCitation author="BECKER V. O." box="[113,308,1641,1668]" pageId="304" pageNumber="441" pagination="53 - 66" refId="ref171495" refString="BECKER V. O. 2013. - Taxonomic changes in the Neotropical Pericopina and Ctenuchina moths (Erebidae, Arctiinae, Arctiini), with description of new taxa. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera 46: 53 - 66." type="journal article" year="2013">Becker (2013: 54)</bibRefCitation>
in the nomenclatural summary of his article, cited “ 
<emphasis box="[322,732,217,1699]" italics="true" pageId="304" pageNumber="441">
<taxonomicName authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker &amp; Espinosa. The" authorityYear="2014" box="[322,643,1673,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudophaloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="304" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="promiscua" status="sp. n.">Pseudophaloe promiscua Becker</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[677,732,217,242]" pageId="304" pageNumber="441" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="BECKER V. O." box="[758,956,216,243]" pageId="304" pageNumber="441" pagination="53 - 66" refId="ref171495" refString="BECKER V. O. 2013. - Taxonomic changes in the Neotropical Pericopina and Ctenuchina moths (Erebidae, Arctiinae, Arctiini), with description of new taxa. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera 46: 53 - 66." type="journal article" year="2013">Becker (2013: 63)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker &amp; Espinosa. The" authorityName="Becker &amp; Espinosa. The" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudophaloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="304" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="promiscua">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="304" pageNumber="441">Pseudophaloe promiscua</emphasis>
Becker &amp; Espinosa. The
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[1084,1183,247,273]" pageId="304" pageNumber="441">holotype</typeStatus>
is housed in INBC where Bernardo Espinoza is, in particular, a specialist of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[974,1075,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="304" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Arctiinae">Arctiinae</taxonomicName>
. It is obvious that Becker wishes to associate Bernardo Espinoza as co-author of this taxon, despite forgetting his name in the nomenclatural summary and its unfortunate mistake in the emendation surname of Bernardo Espinoza.
</paragraph>
